<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-199-152 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 542 737</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  March 18 1991 v10 n6 p26(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GSA, ATandamp;T find FTS security in Pyramid. (General ServicesAdministration, FTS 2000 network, Pyramid Development Corp.'sPC/DACS security software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Masud, S.A.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Contracts)Pyramid Development Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Product:   PC/DACS (Data security software) (Usage).andO;Topic:     United States. General Services AdministrationFederal Telecommunications System 2000 (Computer network)Data SecuritySecurity SoftwareNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GSA, ATandamp;T Find FTS Security in PyramidandM;The General Services Administration and ATandamp;T Co. will use Pyramid DevelopmentCorp.'s workstation security software to protect information connected withATandamp;T's portion of the FTS 2000 network.andM;Don Frick, ATandamp;T's FTS 2000 information security managerk, said PC/DACS wasselected from among 10 top security products by ATandamp;T employees involved inthe FTS 2000 program and by the company's Bell Laboratories unit.andM;&quot;A testing methodology was designed, written and implemented exclusively forthis project.andP;  In addition, a testing laboratory was put into place where theproducts were evaluated against the methodology.andP;  The entire process took sixmonths to complete,&quot; Frick said.andM;ATandamp;T will run PC/DAS, which operates on any IBM or compatible PC with atleast 512K or RAM running MS-DOS 2.0 or higher, on 16-MHz 386 micros.andM;Frick said both ATandamp;T and the General Services Administration use thesemachines for the FTS 2000 Management Information System.andM;The official said ATandamp;T has purchased 650 site licenses for the software fromthe Rocky Hill, Conn., company.andM;In 1989, PC/DACS was issued a D level certification by the National ComputerSecurity Center.andM;Gary Lynch, a regional manager for Pyramid, said other federal users ofPC/DACS include the FBI and NASA.andP;  It has a GSA schedule price of $149 for asingle copy.andO;</TEXT></DOC>